===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
{{en-noun}}

# {{context|grammar|lang=en}} A construction showing a [[relative]] [[quality]], in English usually formed by adding ''[[more]]'' or appending ''[[-er]]''. For example, the comparative of ''green'' is ''greener''; of ''evil'', ''more evil''.
# {{context|grammar|lang=en}} A word in the '''comparative''' form.
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} An [[equal]]; a [[rival]]; a [[compeer]].
#* Beaumont and Flanders
#*: Gerard ever was / His full '''comparative'''.
# {{context|obsolete|lang=en}} One who makes [[comparison]]s; one who [[affect]]s [[wit]].
#* Shakespeare
#*: Every beardless vain '''comparative'''.

